  "texts": [
    "LangChain [53] provides a modular framework for chaining LLM calls with external tools (e.g., APIs and databases) and memory systems, offering flexibility for customizable agent pipelines.",
    "MetaGPT [37] simulates software development teams with role-based agents (e.g., product managers and engineers) that follow structured workflows, enhancing multi-agent collaboration.",
    "Other notable frameworks include BabyAGI [54], which focuses on task-driven autonomous iteration, and CAMEL [47], which explores role-playing agent societies with communicative agents.",
    "Table VI shows the comparisons of mainstream open-source multi-agent frameworks.2) Roadmap: Existing representative industrial practices include computer use, AI smartphones, Anthropic's model context protocol (MCP) [13], and Google's agent-to-agent (A2A) Protocol [9].",
    "(i) Computer-Use Agents (CUAs): As existing Internet services are originally built for humans, CUAs [14] such as OpenAI's Operator mimic human GUI interactions (e.g., mouse clicks and keystrokes) to drive browsers and mobile interfaces, but incur significant screen-scraping overhead that undermines agent efficiency."
  ],
